Willow Street, West side, at Orange Street. The vacant lots at the right, north of Orange Street, were the site of the Merriam House.
1924.

707417f-a.text:
58-72 Willow Street, west side, between Orange Street,(right) and Pine. apple Street (left). The white house in the foreground, is known as the
Putman House.
August 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

707418f-a.text:
62-72 Willow Street, west side, between Orange and Pineapple Streets, showing the white house built by Adrian Van Sinderen in 1828. On the site ot the house at the extreme left, was a frame house occupied by
Erastus Beadle, who published the Beadle dime novels.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
